
# Spring Outing Survey PRD

## 1. Overview
A web-based form application to collect and organize information for a spring outing trip to Beijing. This form will help gather participant details, preferences, and logistical information to facilitate trip planning.

## 2. User Roles
- Trip Organizer (Admin)
- Participants

## 3. Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Participant Information Section
- Personal details (Name, Contact number, WeChat ID)
- Emergency contact information
- Dietary restrictions/allergies
- Special needs/accessibility requirements

### 3.2 Trip Preferences
- Available dates selection (multiple choice)
- Preferred activities (checkboxes):
  - Historical sites (Forbidden City, Summer Palace)
  - Modern attractions (Olympic Park, 798 Art Zone)
  - Hiking (Great Wall sections)
  - Food tours
  - Shopping
- Transportation preferences (bus, subway, walking)
- Budget range selection

### 3.3 Logistics
- Accommodation preferences (hotel, hostel, shared rooms)
- Willingness to carpool
- T-shirt size (for group merchandise)

### 3.4 Admin Features
- Real-time response dashboard
- Export to Excel/CSV functionality
- Basic analytics (participant counts, preference statistics)
- Email/SMS notification system for updates

## 4. Non-Functional Requirements
- Mobile-responsive design
- Chinese language support
- Form submission deadline reminder
- Data privacy compliance (GDPR-like protections)
- Cloud storage for responses

## 5. Technical Specifications
- Frontend: React.js with Ant Design components
- Backend: Node.js with Express
- Database: MongoDB for flexible schema
- Hosting: Alibaba Cloud or Tencent Cloud for China accessibility

## 6. Success Metrics
- 90% participant completion rate
- Submission of all required fields enforced
- Average completion time under 5 minutes
- 24-hour response time for organizer follow-ups

## 7. Future Enhancements
- Payment integration for deposits
- Group chat feature
- Itinerary builder based on responses
- Weather integration for date recommendations
